Description: To: kelly_needham@vfc.com CC:  BCC: emaccountmanagers@elitemeet.us Attachment: EliteMeet Dallas July 2019.pdf  Subject: Elite Meet webinar Body:  	 	 	 	 	 	 	Hi Kelly, 	 	  Thanks for the dates/times, I will quickly poll our community to find the consensus and provide the dial-in info. Would you or your teammates have any issues if we recorded our session? We do so to ensure widest distro for folks that can't attend, so if anyone has druthers please let me know. 	 	  A few of the things I promised, below is a generic agenda for your consideration, by no means is it firm so please feel free to adjust as needed. And 2nd, attached is our EM-Dallas flyer for your consideration, we hope you or your team will be able to attend. 	 	  I'll send our community demographics in a follow-up email (sorry for spamming your inbox) so you have context for what the Elite Meet veteran community looks like as a run-up to the webinar. 	 	Draft agenda: 	Pre webinar: read ahead / fact sheet (company to EM; EM to VF), VF bios, vet bios (if registered early) 	 	Webinar (~1 hour total): 	- Intros (name, job, location) 	-(handoff to VF) VF orientation 	-Culture 	-Possible / historical veteran roles in VFC 	-Application process 	- Current priority fills / locations  	Q&A (min 15min) 	-sample jobs - senior/mid manager to executive - right fit (have example handy - fighter pilot +10yr/ SOF vet 10-15+yr)? 	-What are your challenges hiring veterans? Or veterans fitting in? 	-Right candidate profile? What do you look for in hiring at manager, senior manager, and executive positions 	 	  If there's anything, please let me know. Thanks again for your support and patience! Hope you have a good Memorial Day weekend! 	 	Cheers, 	 	Dave Low 	Account Manager | Elite Meet 	808.398.6527 	EMaccountmanagers@elitemeet.us

If you have any questions or need anything please do not hesitate to reach out. 	 	 	Best Regards, 	 	Henry D. Ages 	Director of Employer Relations | Elite Meet 	334.447.0901 	Henry@elitemeet.us
